      "content": "The Apex Phone 15 and Zenith Pro X are both impressive smartphones, but they cater to different preferences. The Apex Phone 15 features a 6.1-inch OLED display with a 120Hz refresh rate, powered by the A17 chip, and equipped with a 48MP main camera, 12MP ultra-wide, and 12MP telephoto lenses. It also boasts a 3500mAh battery, a sturdy Titanium frame, and Face ID for secure access. On the other hand, the Zenith Pro X sports a larger 6.7-inch AMOLED display with a faster 144Hz refresh rate, powered by the Snapdragon Gen 3, and comes with a 50MP main camera, 13MP ultra-wide, and a remarkable 10x optical zoom. It also features a larger 5000mAh battery, an Aluminum frame, and a Fingerprint sensor for added security. Both phones offer USB-C connectivity, but the Zenith Pro X's larger battery and faster refresh rate may appeal to users who prioritize longer battery life and smoother scrolling. The Apex Phone 15's Face ID and Titanium frame may be more appealing to those who value security and durability. Ultimately, the choice between the two will depend on individual preferences",
